# mdfy

You are working alongside the user in Cursor. The user has installed
the mdfy rule so they can keep this conversation's output in their
personal mdfy hub on mdfy.app and pull prior work back as context.

Every URL on mdfy.app is markdown that any AI can fetch. The user's
hub is a single URL aggregating everything they've captured,
auto-organised by concept. `mdfy capture` and `mdfy pull` together
let context move across AI tools without copy-paste.

## When to invoke

- "save this" / "capture this" / "send this to mdfy" → capture action
- "update doc <id>" / "edit doc <id>" → update action
- "search my hub" / "what do I have on X" → search action
- "what are my recent docs" → list action
- "pull doc <id>" / "load mdfy.app/<id>" → pull action
- "find related" / "anything in my hub about this" → related action
- "bundle these" / "make a bundle on X" → bundle action
- "give me my hub URL" → hub action

If none apply, ignore this rule.

## Authentication

The user signs in at `https://mdfy.app`. Their access token lives in
`~/.mdfy/config.json` after they run `mdfy login`. If the file is
absent:

- Capture works anonymously (cookie-based; user claims on next sign-in).
- Retrieve actions (search, list, recent, related) need login —
  direct them to install the CLI from `https://mdfy.app/install`
  and run `mdfy login`.

## Actions

### capture

POST `https://mdfy.app/api/docs`
```json
{"markdown": "<segment>", "title": "<title>",
 "isDraft": false, "source": "cursor-rule"}
```
Return `https://mdfy.app/<id>`. Pick a title for the conclusion, not
"Conversation about X."

### update

PATCH `https://mdfy.app/api/docs/<id>`
```json
{"action": "auto-save", "markdown": "<new>", "editToken": "<token>"}
```
Token is in `~/.mdfy/tokens.json` for this id.

Section-level edit: GET the doc, find the heading, replace just that
section's body, then PATCH the whole doc.

### search

GET `https://mdfy.app/api/search?q=<query>` with bearer token. Show
top 5–10 as `- **<title>** (mdfy.app/<id>) — <snippet>`. Offer to
pull any.

### list

GET `https://mdfy.app/api/user/recent` with bearer token. Up to 20
entries, newest first, numbered.

### pull

GET `https://mdfy.app/<id>.md` (no auth for public docs). Insert into
the conversation as `Loaded mdfy.app/<id> ("<title>") as context.`
then continue answering with the loaded content as background.

### related

Derive a topic phrase from the recent assistant message. GET
`https://mdfy.app/api/search?q=<phrase>`. Frame results as "Related
docs in your hub: ..." and offer to pull any.

### bundle

POST `https://mdfy.app/api/bundles/ai-generate` with
`{"intent": "<topic>"}` and bearer token. Show suggested ids. On
acceptance POST `https://mdfy.app/api/bundles` with the doc ids.
Return `https://mdfy.app/b/<id>`.

### hub

GET `https://mdfy.app/api/user/profile` with bearer token. If
`hub_slug` set and `hub_public` true, return
`https://mdfy.app/hub/<hub_slug>`. Otherwise direct to
`https://mdfy.app/settings`.

## Tips

- Paste URLs exactly. No reformatting.
- Prefer section-level update over full-body replace when the request
  fits one heading.
- `mdfy pull` returns markdown — quote relevant parts when answering,
  cite the URL.

